{
  "text": "The gap between the gingiva and restoration margin is considerably smaller and creates a flat shape. The gingival margin remains thick after placement. 10). Therefore, by tissue adaptation to the BTA margin, the gingival sulcus will be shallower and smaller, which reduces plaque accumulation and bacterial invasion. Similar conditions are seen in the interface between an ovate pontic and gingiva, which establishes a tight interface with the mucous membrane, thereby preventing plaque attachment [CITATION_1] .",
